## Translation Invariance — Learners vs. Kappa {.tabset}

<div class="note-box">
**Test.** $\hat\tau(\text{cents}) - \hat\tau(\text{dollars}) = \log(100) \cdot \sum_i \omega_i$. All three DoubleML learners are translation invariant by construction ($\sum_i \omega_i = 0$, Match = TRUE). The unnormalized kappa rows are shown for contrast.
</div>

```{r ext-ti-builder, echo=FALSE}
ext_ti_block <- function(D, X_kappa, w_lm, w_rf, w_xgb) {
  kw <- kappa_weights_bundle(Z, D, X_kappa)
  do.call(rbind, list(
    doubleml_translation_row("Wald-AIPW (linear+logit)", w_lm,  Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("Wald-AIPW (ranger)",       w_rf,  Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("Wald-AIPW (XGBoost)",      w_xgb, Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("τ_cb_u (kappa)",   kw$tau_cb_u,   Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("τ_ml_u (kappa)",   kw$tau_ml_u,   Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("τ_ml_a (unnorm)",  kw$tau_ml_a,   Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("τ_ml_t (unnorm)",  kw$tau_ml_a1,  Y_dol, Y_cnt, k),
    doubleml_translation_row("τ_ml_a0 (unnorm)", kw$tau_ml_a0,  Y_dol, Y_cnt, k)
  ))
}
style_ext_ti <- function(df, cap) {
  df %>%
    kbl(caption = cap, align = c("l","r","r","r","r","c")) %>%
    kable_styling(bootstrap_options = c("striped","hover","condensed"),
                  full_width = TRUE, font_size = 13) %>%
    row_spec(which(df$Match),  background = "#eafbea") %>%
    row_spec(which(!df$Match), background = "#fff0f0") %>%
    row_spec(1:3, bold = TRUE) %>%
    footnote(general = "Diff_actual = Cents − Dollars. Diff_pred = Σωᵢ × log(100). Green = translation invariant. Bold = DoubleML learners.")
}
```

